**Linux Practice \- Process and Services**

**Command:** ps \-ef | head  
**Observation:** PID 1 is systemd, which is the parent of all user-space processes.   
![][image1]

**Command:** top  
**Observation:** System load average is 0.00 and CPU is 100% idle. No high CPU-consuming processes were observed.  
![][image2]

**Command:** pgrep sshd  
**Observation:** It searches for **running processes** and returns their **PID(s)** (Process ID).  
![][image3]

**Command:** systemctl list-units \--type=service \--state=running | head  
**Observation:** Identified active systemd services like cron, ssh, docker, and containerd running on the system.  
![][image4]

**Command:** systemctl status cron  
**Observation:** cron service is enabled and running. Recent logs show hourly cron jobs executing successfully.  
![][image5]

**Command:** journalctl \-u cron  
**Observation:** Cron logs show regular execution of scheduled jobs with no errors.  
![][image6]

**Command:** tail \-n 20 /var/log/syslog  
**Observation:** System logs show normal cron and sysstat activity. Noticed amazon-ssm-agent errors due to missing EC2 IAM role configuration  
![][image7]

**Command:** systemctl restart cron  
**Observation:** cron service restarted successfully and is running with a new PID.  
![][image8]
